The projection of $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix}$ onto $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$ is a scalar multiple of $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix},$ say $k \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.$  We want
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} = k \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.\][asy]
usepackage("amsmath");

unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair A, B, P, Q;

A = (4,5);
B = (2,0);
P = (A + reflect(B,(0,1))*A)/2;
Q = P - (0,0.5);

draw((-1,0)--(5,0));
