Then
\begin{align*}
k &= \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}} \\
&= \frac{8}{4} \\
&= 2.
\end{align*}Therefore, the projection is $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}.$
